net.sf.tweety.logics.cl

Class RuleBasedCReasoner

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.tweety.commons.Reasoner
      • net.sf.tweety.logics.cl.RuleBasedCReasoner

  • public class RuleBasedCReasoner
extends net.sf.tweety.commons.Reasoner
    This is a reasoner using c-representation and rules to solve these c-representations. It contains a list of rules whereby the first rule is the rule with the highest priorization, that means it is applied first.
    Author:
    Tim Janus

      • process

        public boolean process()
        Processes the kappa values using the rules stored in the prioritzed rule list. It applies the rules by their priority until no changes occurred after every rule is applied.
        Returns:
        true if the processing of the kappa values is complete, false if it is not complete.

      • isComplete

        public boolean isComplete()
        Checks every kappa value.
        Returns:
        true if every kappa value is evaluated, false otherwise
